SIMPLE: butting_joint
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Butting joint
<hw>But"ting joint`</hw>. <def>A joint between two pieces of timber or
wood, at the end of one or both, and either at right angles or oblique
to the grain, as the joints which the struts and braces form with the
truss posts; -- sometimes called <xex>abutting joint</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Butt joint</ent>⟦br⟧
